description.plain:
Agar Agar est un duo electro-pop français composé de Clara Cappagli et d'Armand Bultheel. Il a sorti en 2016 son premier EP intitulé Cardan.

Agar Agar is a french Electro-Pop duo composed of Clara Cappagli and Arman Bultheel. In 2016 they released their debut EP titled Cardan, and in 2018 their first album The Dog and the Future.

description.plain:
The first song of Agar Agar’s debut album “Cardan” depicts the feeling of loneliness and isolation inside a big city.

Through the song the narrator describes her constant search for fulfillment and happiness. A few times the narrator briefly seems to have found what she was looking for but then shortly after continuous her search. So it seems as if she can only experience happiness for a brief amount of time through possibly drug use and/or sex while still lacking what she is truly desiring. The song also implies that the narrator has been dealing with suicidal thoughts: “Or I’m just gonna throw something in the bathtub now”.

description.plain: Requiem is about an undefined relationship between two girls. One of them is angry at the other one for not caring about other people such as herself. This song’s trippy synths and Clara Cappagli’s meaningful voice are agonizing in sorrow since the other girl destroyed their relationship and probably other ones.

description.plain:
This song is filled with references to life simulation video game The Sims : “motherlode” is a cheat code that gives your household 50,000 in game currency, animal friend is one the traits you can choose for your Sim, a house with basketball court floors is something you can create in the game because you can customize your house however you want! Skills and hygiene also terms from the games.

The French duo said that they were inspired from The Sims while making this album in several interviews:

While composing the music for our album, we started to play The Sims all day long. Like, at least five hours a day. So at some point, reality and fiction blurred.
